&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dbtsai&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dbtsai&quot;&gt;dbtsai&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hvanhovell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hvanhovell&quot;&gt;hvanhovell&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15976192" author="dbtsai" created="Thu, 20 Apr 2017 06:50:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=viirya&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;viirya&quot;&gt;viirya&lt;/a&gt;. We ran into this bugs while migrating from Spark 1.6 to Spark 2.0, and this breaks all our production jobs. I&apos;ll argue that the behavior should not be changed in the unescaped sql string in parser. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
